title: IGEL: A 3D Shape Modeling Tool Mimicking Heat Cutter
title_en: IGEL: A 3D Shape Modeling Tool Mimicking Heat Cutter
abstract: 本研究はヒートカッターによるスチレンフォーム加工操作を模倣する3Dモデリング手法を提案している。提案手法はユーザが金属線状の刃形状をスケッチで指定し、2D/3Dモードの切替や直線近似によって処理を軽減しながら、三角メッシュ化したスチレンフォームを切断して多様な形状を作成する仕組みを実装している。
abstract_en: This work proposes a 3D modeling method that mimics heat-cutter operations for shaping styrofoam. The proposed method lets users sketch the wire-like cutter shape and uses 2D/3D mode switching and linear approximation to reduce processing while triangulating and cutting the styrofoam to produce varied shapes.
positioning_summary: 本研究は既存の3DCGツールが自由に曲げられる刃や直感的な切断操作を表現できない問題を解決することを位置づけとしている。位置づけとして本研究はスチレンフォームを用いた造形作業における操作性と効率の不足を対象にしている。
positioning_summary_en: This work is positioned to solve the inability of existing 3D graphics tools to represent bendable cutters and intuitive cutting operations. This work targets the lack of usability and efficiency in shaping styrofoam during fabrication tasks.
purpose_summary: 本研究の目的はヒートカッター特有の自由に曲げられる刃と少ないストロークで直感的に形状を作る操作を再現し、モデリングの柔軟性を高めることである。目的として本研究はスチレンフォームを扱う造形ユーザの作業効率向上を目標にしている。
purpose_summary_en: The purpose of this work is to reproduce the bendable blade and intuitive low-stroke cutting operations characteristic of a heat cutter to increase modeling flexibility. The purpose of this work is to improve the work efficiency of fabrication users who handle styrofoam.
method_summary: 本システムはユーザが2Dモードでカッター形状をスケッチし、スケッチ曲線を直線近似してノード数と処理を低減するインタフェースを採用している。方法として本システムはユーザ設計のカッターで三角メッシュ化したスチレンフォームを切断し、波状や円形など多様な形状を生成するメッシュ切断機構を実装している。
method_summary_en: This system adopts an interface where the user sketches the cutter shape in 2D mode and approximates the sketch curves by line segments to reduce node count and processing. As a method, this system triangulates the styrofoam and uses the user-designed cutter to cut the mesh, producing varied shapes such as wavy and circular forms.
evaluation_summary: 本研究は実装と事例検証を用いてシステムを評価している。評価では2Dの直線近似が新規ノード数と処理時間を大幅に削減し、波状カッターが二ストロークで波状表面を生成し、円形スケッチが差集合に相当する形状を生成できることが確認されたという結果を報告している。
evaluation_summary_en: This work evaluated the system through implementation and case-study validation. The evaluation reports that the 2D linear approximation greatly reduced the number of new nodes and processing time, that the wavy cutter produced a wavy surface in two strokes, and that a circular sketch generated a shape equivalent to a difference operation.

Paper summary:
Title: IGEL: A 3D Shape Modeling Tool Mimicking Heat Cutter
Authors: Hitomi Imaizumi, Ito Takayuki
Year: 2008
Abstract: This work proposes a 3D modeling method that mimics heat-cutter operations for shaping styrofoam. The proposed method lets users sketch the wire-like cutter shape and uses 2D/3D mode switching and linear approximation to reduce processing while triangulating and cutting the styrofoam to produce varied shapes.
Positioning Summary: This work is positioned to solve the inability of existing 3D graphics tools to represent bendable cutters and intuitive cutting operations. This work targets the lack of usability and efficiency in shaping styrofoam during fabrication tasks.
Purpose Summary: The purpose of this work is to reproduce the bendable blade and intuitive low-stroke cutting operations characteristic of a heat cutter to increase modeling flexibility. The purpose of this work is to improve the work efficiency of fabrication users who handle styrofoam.
Method Summary: This system adopts an interface where the user sketches the cutter shape in 2D mode and approximates the sketch curves by line segments to reduce node count and processing. As a method, this system triangulates the styrofoam and uses the user-designed cutter to cut the mesh, producing varied shapes such as wavy and circular forms.
Evaluation Summary: This work evaluated the system through implementation and case-study validation. The evaluation reports that the 2D linear approximation greatly reduced the number of new nodes and processing time, that the wavy cutter produced a wavy surface in two strokes, and that a circular sketch generated a shape equivalent to a difference operation.
